President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. These appointments include Susan Athey as a member of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science, Judge Wm. Terrell Hodges as a member of the Board of Trustees of the James Madison Memorial Fellowship Foundation, Robert Stanton as a member of the Board of Trustees of the American Folklife Center at the Library of Congress, Bill Stetson as a member of the Advisory Committee on the Arts for the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts, Brady J. Deaton as Chairman of the Board for International Food and Agricultural Development, Gebisa Ejeta as a member of the Board for International Food and Agricultural Development, Jo Luck as a member of the Board for International Food and Agricultural Development, Marty McVey as a member of the Board for International Food and Agricultural Development, David Blitzstein as a member of the Advisory Committee to the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation, and Joyce Mader as a member of the Advisory Committee to the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation. Each individual brings unique qualifications and experience to their respective roles.